blog.title: Jodi
blog.description: I'm just a tired bitch that's loves all things Bellarke and Jonrya/Jonerys

body:
Unpopular opinion

But I hope that Jon (actually Jon, not fucking Arya) is the one to kill Daenerys. I want him to do it, and I want him to be in agony. I want him to look into her eyes as he plunges his sword through her heart. Because he will remember this moment for the rest of his life. And I want him to be very emotional. Since this show loves repeating the fucking past, might as well go out with a bang. Two of his lovers both dying in his arms. This moment will haunt him for eternity as he lives off in exile. If Dany can’t get a happy ending, than neither can he. His fate is almost worse than death.

tags: a song of ice and fire
no dany its not your fault
body:
Got S08E05

NO. JUST NO. I won’t blame my wonderful characters. These so well mentally developed characters. I refuse to blame them. Though I feel betrayed, the treason didn’t come from them, it’s not their fault. In my heart I hold DnD deeply responsible and that will change when the sun rises in the West and sets in the East. But it still hurts and it will always do, as it seems we lost some old friends (by force obviously) , because they changed beyond recognition.

summary: I’m enjoying Game of Thrones this season. I feel like whatever they did, some viewers would have found fault because the show is...
body: I’m enjoying Game of Thrones this season. I feel like whatever they did, some viewers would have found fault because the show is so so hyped up and it’s impossible to please everyone. Yes, of course I would have written certain storylines slightly differently if I was in charge but part of Game of Thrones’ appeal to me is that not everything works out the way we expect it to. People have the right to a negative opinion, of course they do. Sometimes it’s a great coping mechanism, to moan. I just prefer to be positive. I’ll just b sitting here, trying to keep things upbeat !
